===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|comete}}, partly from {{inh|en|ang|comēta}} and partly from {{der|en|fro|comete}}, both from {{der|en|la|comētēs}}, from {{der|en|grc|κομήτης|t=longhaired}}, short for ἀστὴρ κομήτης ([astēr] komētēs, "longhaired [star])" and referring to the tail of a comet, from {{m|grc|κόμη|t=hair}}. Compare {{noncog|en|faxed star}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|kŏm'ət}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈkɒmət/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-comet.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɒmɪt|s=2}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|astronomy}} A [[celestial body]] consisting mainly of [[ice]], [[dust]] and [[gas]] in a (usually very [[eccentric]]) [[orbit]] around the [[Sun]] and having a "tail" of matter blown back from it by the [[solar wind]] as it approaches the Sun.
# A [[celestial]] [[phenomenon]] with the appearance given by the [[orbiting]] celestial [[body]].
# Any of several species of [[hummingbird]] found in the [[Andes]].

